![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1578252067634-25KLHOFACVPG2W8RS00F/image-asset.jpeg?format=original)

80 Years ago, draped in a dark cape and cowl, complete with fashionable purple gloves, Batman made his debut in the pages of Detective Comics #27. Fast forward to 2019, where the 1000th issue of this historically long running comic, promises to give us all the feels as Nostalgia takes a trip to Gotham City. Complete with stories written by visionary writers Scott Snyder, Tom King, and Paul Dini, Detective #1000 is the trip down memory lane that we hoped it would be, and the guys at CBC go into the rabbit hole, in this jam packed episode that pays tribute to all things Detective Comics!

If you can, please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the one stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  
  
